&lt;h3 id=&quot;mouseArea__POTENTIALCF1&quot; class=&quot;tabDiv pR dblClk  new-hover-detail-info&quot; data-params=&quot;{&amp;quot;isUniqueField&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;false&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;mandate&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;false&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;customfield&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;true&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;maxlength&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;6000&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displaylabel&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;About Us&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;decimalLength&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;defaultvalue&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;A.J. Boggs &amp;amp; Company is an equal opportunity employer.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment on the basis of merit and fitness and without discrimination on the basis of race, color, creed, national origin, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender expression, disability, weight, height, marital status, age or political affiliation (except where any such criterion constitutes a bona fide occupational qualification).\r\n\r\nWe take pride and joy in applying technologies and developing innovative solutions to important problems. We are a growing, US-based, information technology (IT) company, looking for people who enjoy working on projects that help people. We are committed to being leaders in the IT industry, maintaining our integrity, and supporting our communities. \r\n\r\nThis job is in a professional, dynamic office environment and part of a vibrant technical community committed to making the world a b

&lt;p&gt;At A.J. Boggs &amp;amp; Company (AJBoggs), we leverage software technology to solve complex challenges. We seek an experienced HR professional to join our team in our Okemos headquarters. You will own a full range of HR functions, including team building, compensation and benefits management, training, and performance rewards. And work collaboratively with our Propower team to acquire talent. This role is central to developing and maintaining the diverse, exceptional teams that drive our success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be willing to work in a rapidly changing environment, be self-managed, and lead process improvement efforts. You’ll need strong writing and leadership skills and be able to lead hiring efforts to source, develop, and promote high performance pros.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role may be right for you if you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer leadership in operational excellence, including recruiting, inspiration, incentives, analysis, planning, project management (budgeting), and performance reward processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the interest and aptitude to understand complex technology and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can contribute to high performance teams, bringing joy and fun to your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong customer service skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;TALENT ACQUISITION&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with our Propower team for full-cycle recruitment to together drive the end-to-end recruitment process for technical and non-technical roles, from initial sourcing to offer negotiation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop Hiring Plans, including position alignment, sourcing, and criteria selection/dev/eval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Sourcing. Develop and execute strategic sourcing plans to identify, engage, and attract top IT professionals in competitive markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate Assessment. Collaborate with the Team Leaders and Position Sponsors to define selection criteria, refine assessment methods, and evaluate candidate fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to target under-represented communities and manage recruitment advertising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems Management. Manage and optimize the use of applicant tracking (ATS-Greenhouse) for efficiency and data integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;HUMAN RESOURCE ADMINISTRATION&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Policy Support: Support the HR Department in the administration, coordination, and evaluation of core HR functions, including policy, procedures, and program development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organization Design: Review and support the development of organizational designs, including refining job description and defining clear roles, policies, and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regulatory Compliance: Collaborate on developing and maintaining programs to ensure compliance with federal, state and local employment, including immigration laws.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Management: develop and manage HR processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outreach: Represent the firm in industry, charitable, and community functions and associations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analysis: Evaluate HR processes, such as benefit cost review, assessment tool&amp;nbsp;effectiveness, project costs, and compensation modeling.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE, KNOWLEDGE, &amp;amp; ABILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Acumen. Communication. Organization Design for Technology Innovation, Promotion, and Delivery. Strategic Consultation. Critical Evaluation. Global and Cultural Awareness. HR Expertise. Leadership and Navigation. Relationship Management. Ethical Practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree and 3-5 years of experience in Human Resources, including benefits and compliance.

&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dedicated, detail-oriented, multi-faceted &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Product Owner&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; with Project Management experience to join our team supporting an online application tailored for healthcare providers. This position is vital in ensuring our customers receive timely and efficient assistance with both technical and business-related issues. The ideal candidate will possess excellent verbal and written communication skills, a strong understanding of product development, technical support processes, aptitude with numbers, and the ability to work cross-functionally to address customer needs and improve customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Feedback &amp;amp; Roadmap Alignment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the bridge between client priorities and the product roadmap—advocating for enhancements that align with both user needs and organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ideation and awareness of industry-related emerging trends that drive existing and new product innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and prioritize bugs, feature requests, and improvement suggestions from clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product Owners and engineering teams to refine the backlog, define acceptance criteria, and track progress through release cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform competitive product analysis and responsive product and marketing strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop team KPIs and other performance measures, such as return on investment goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze recurring support trends to identify opportunities for product optimization and process improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project &amp;amp; Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary front-line point of contact for clients throughout the full lifecycle of engagement, coordinating communication, managing expectations related to scope and timelines, and ensuring a high-quality client experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead planning, coordination, and delivery of software implementation and integration projects (e.g., Lifia Portal and data integration projects).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain detailed project plans, schedules, and deliverables using Agile and/or hybrid methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track progress against milestones, manage risks and dependencies, and proactively communicate updates with clients and internal leadership to ensure alignment on scope, timeline, and delivery expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate go-live readiness, testing activities, and transition to ongoing support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate recurring project meetings, prepare progress reports, and communicate status with clients and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain awareness of client missions (e.g., public health, government programs) and applicable regulatory requirements, ensuring all work is delivered in a compliant manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business &amp;amp; Systems Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead client discovery sessions with stakeholders and end-users to understand system goals, user workflows, business processes, and data requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and communicate system architecture, data integrations (APIs, HL7/FHIR), and hosting/security considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate functional requirements into clear specifications for development and configuration teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document current and future state processes, data flows, and system interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate that delivered solutions meet user needs through acceptance testing and user feedback sessions; and identify opportunities for system improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/str
